ou kay. so the problem is, that the validator decorators in https://github.com/plone/plone.api/blob/master/src/plone/api/validation.py does not support "either one of this set of parameters or one of the other".

this could be solved, if the ``required_parameters`` would be extended to catch ``MissingParameterError`` and revalidate against another set of parameters, so that you can write:

```
@required_parameters('body')
@required_parameters('recipient', 'subject', 'body')
def send_email(...):
    ...
```

Oh, it would be nice, if the required parameters would support typing too, like:
``@required_parameters('body', types={'body': email.Email})``

